

Parallel Essay Review Agent API

This project is an AI-powered essay evaluation system built using FastAPI and LangGraph. It processes a given essay through multiple evaluation pipelines in parallel and returns structured feedback along with a final score.

⸻

Overview

The system uses a parallel agent-based workflow to analyze an essay across multiple dimensions instead of relying on a single sequential evaluation. Each agent focuses on a specific aspect of writing, and the results are aggregated into a final response.

⸻

Features
	•	Parallel essay evaluation using LangGraph
	•	Multi-dimensional analysis:
	•	Language quality
	•	Depth of analysis
	•	Clarity of thought
	•	Aggregated feedback and scoring
	•	FastAPI-based REST API
	•	Local model support via Ollama
	•	Docker support for deployment

⸻

Architecture

Client applications send requests to the FastAPI server. The backend uses a LangGraph workflow to execute multiple evaluation agents in parallel. Each agent processes the essay independently, and the results are combined before returning a response.

⸻

Tech Stack
	•	FastAPI
	•	LangGraph
	•	Ollama (default model: qwen3:8b)
	•	Docker

⸻

API Endpoints

GET /home_test

Health check endpoint.

POST /review

Processes an essay and returns structured feedback.

Request Example

{
  "essay": "Your essay text here..."
}

Response Example

{
  "language_feedback": "...",
  "depth_feedback": "...",
  "clarity_feedback": "...",
  "final_score": 8.2,
  "summary": "Overall evaluation summary"
}


⸻

Local Setup

1. Start Ollama

ollama pull qwen3:8b
ollama serve

2. Setup Environment

python -m venv myenv
source myenv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Run Server

uvicorn fast_api:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000


⸻

Using API Keys

Update the .env file with your API key if using external providers. The default configuration uses a local Ollama model.

⸻

Docker Usage

Build Image

docker build -t parallel-graph:latest .

Run Container

docker run --rm --name parallel-graph -p 8000:8000 --env-file .env parallel-graph:latest

With Host Ollama

docker run --rm --name parallel-graph -p 8000:8000 \
--env-file .env \
-e OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434 \
parallel-graph:latest

Stop Container

docker stop parallel-graph


⸻

API Test

curl -X POST "http://127.0.0.1:8000/review" \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"essay":"Technology has changed education in many ways..."}'


